Spination and scopula: palp: tibia with 5 spines, v3 p2, tarsus scopulate, v2, leg I: Patella and femur without spines, tibia, v1, metatarsus scopula covers all, v4, tarsus scopula on ventral without spines. leg II: patella and femur without spines, tibia, v4, metatarsus scopulate on its distal half, v6, tarsus scopula covers all, without spines. leg III: tibia, r5 p2 d1, leg III: metatarsus has 17 spines, v6 r5 p4 d2, leg III: tibia, r5 p2 d1, leg III: metatarsus, p4 r6 v7. Preening combs on distal ventral metatarsi I–III. Legs (
Table 2
